'''Antonovych prize''' (Omelian and Tetiana Antonovych Foundation Award) – yearly award given for literary works written in [[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] and for research on [[Ukrainian studies]]. The award is given by the Omelian and Tetiana Antonovych Foundation since 1981. The size of award is $10,000 USD. The laureates are chosen by the jury, while nominations can be made by the members of jury, individuals or institutions. The laureates make a speech during the award ceremony.<ref name="BihunAwards">{{cite news|last1=Bihun|first1=Yaro|title=Two historians are honored with 2012 Antonovych Awards|url=https://search.proquest.com/news/docview/1260701746/fulltext/1D770134A6E746F2PQ/5?accountid=10226|accessdate=29 August 2017|publisher=[[Ukrainian Weekly]]|date=2 December 2012}}</ref>
